The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 May is 41,971 (4,857.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 April, there were 131 new confirmed cases (15.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 April, there were 126 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% (5 extra cases).
